==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the [[astronomer]] Johannes Hevelius in 1662.  From {{L.}} ''[[mirus]]'', "wonderful, surprising"

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Mira'''

#{{star}}: A [[binary]] star in the [[constellation]] [[Cetus]]; Omicron (ο) Boötis.  The system contains a variable [[red giant]] and a [[white dwarf]].  Its brightness varies from a [[magnitude]] 2 at its brightest to a magnitude 10 at its dimmest.

